---
// Custom landing page (English) — bypasses Starlight's docs layout
import '../../styles/landing.css';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<html lang="en">
<head>
	<meta charset="utf-8" />
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
	<title>memtomem — Long &amp; Short-Term Memory Infrastructure for AI Agents</title>
	<meta name="description" content="Index your markdown notes, docs, and code into a searchable knowledge base for any AI agent. STM + LTM architecture for persistent, cross-agent memory." />
	<meta name="theme-color" content="#534AB7" />
	<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href={`${base}/favicon.svg`} />
</head>
<body>

<nav class="nav">
	<a href={`${base}/en/`} class="nav-logo"><span>mem</span>to<span>mem</span></a>
	<div class="nav-links">
		<a href={`${base}/en/guides/quickstart/`}>Docs</a>
		<a href="#architecture">Architecture</a>
		<a href={`${base}/en/reference/api/`}>API</a>
		<a href="https://github.com/memtomem/memtomem">GitHub</a>
		<span class="nav-lang"><a href={`${base}/`}>KO</a></span>
	</div>
	<a href={`${base}/en/guides/quickstart/`}>
		<button class="nav-cta">Get started</button>
	</a>
</nav>

<section class="hero">
	<div class="hero-badge">Open Source · Apache 2.0</div>
	<h1>AI That Never Forgets —<br /><em>Memory Infrastructure</em> for Agents</h1>
	<p class="hero-sub">
		Index your markdown notes, documents, and code into a searchable knowledge base
		for any AI agent. STM + LTM architecture preserves memory across sessions
		and shares knowledge between agents.
	</p>
	<div class="hero-install">
		<span class="dollar">$</span> uv tool install memtomem
	</div>
	<div class="hero-stats">
		<div><strong>84</strong>MCP Tools</div>
		<div><strong>10</strong>Compression</div>
		<div><strong>6+</strong>Runtimes</div>
		<div><strong>0</strong>GPU Required</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section class="section">
	<div class="section-inner">
		<div class="section-label">Problem</div>
		<div class="section-title">Why Do Agents Forget?</div>
		<div class="section-desc">Tool integration (MCP), safety (Guardrails), and observability (Langfuse) are mature — but the memory layer still has no standard.</div>
		<div class="problem-grid">
			<div class="problem-card">
				<div class="problem-num">1</div>
				<h3>No Memory Between Sessions</h3>
				<p>All context is lost when a session ends. Architecture decisions, coding patterns, and debugging history must be re-explained every time.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="problem-card">
				<div class="problem-num">2</div>
				<h3>Memory Silos Between Agents</h3>
				<p>Knowledge from Claude Code can't be carried over to Gemini CLI. Each agent is trapped in its own isolated memory silo.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="problem-card">
				<div class="problem-num">3</div>
				<h3>Limitations of Existing Solutions</h3>
				<p>Current memory systems only work when agents explicitly search, are locked to specific runtimes, and offer only a single LTM layer.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section class="section">
	<div class="section-inner">
		<div class="section-label">Solution</div>
		<div class="section-title">memtomem Solves This</div>
		<div class="section-desc">Applying the cognitive science working-memory / long-term memory model to agents. Short-term compression and long-term search as independent MCP servers.</div>
		<div class="feature-grid">
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="feature-icon" style="background: var(--accent-light); color: var(--accent);">S</div>
				<h3>Proactive Surfacing</h3>
				<p>Automatically inject relevant memories without agent request. 5-level relevance gating + feedback auto-tuning.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="feature-icon" style="background: var(--teal-light); color: var(--teal);">G</div>
				<h3>MCP Proxy Gateway</h3>
				<p>STM sits between agent and server as a transparent proxy. Memory injection into all MCP calls — no code changes.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="feature-icon" style="background: var(--coral-light); color: var(--coral);">C</div>
				<h3>Cross-Runtime Sync</h3>
				<p>Context Gateway auto-syncs agent definitions, skills, and commands across 6 runtimes.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="feature-icon" style="background: #FAEEDA; color: #854F0B;">10</div>
				<h3>10 Compression Strategies</h3>
				<p>Auto-selected by content type. Progressive delivery for zero information loss.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="feature-icon" style="background: #E6F1FB; color: #185FA5;">A</div>
				<h3>Multi-Agent Knowledge Sharing</h3>
				<p>Namespace isolation + sharing. Agent→Agent, Human→Agent — knowledge flows in all directions.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="feature-card">
				<div class="feature-icon" style="background: #EAF3DE; color: #3B6D11;">L</div>
				<h3>Fully Local</h3>
				<p>SQLite + ONNX. No GPU, no external services. 100% data sovereignty.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="architecture">
	<div class="section-inner">
		<div class="section-label">Architecture</div>
		<div class="section-title">Two-Layer Architecture</div>
		<div class="section-desc">STM proxy and LTM server connected via MCP, transparently providing memory to all agents.</div>
		<div class="arch-diagram">
			<div class="arch-label">AI Agents / Frameworks</div>
			<div class="arch-row">
				<div class="arch-node">Claude Code</div>
				<div class="arch-node">Gemini CLI</div>
				<div class="arch-node">Codex CLI</div>
				<div class="arch-node">Cursor</div>
				<div class="arch-node">LangGraph</div>
			</div>
			<div class="arch-arrow">↓ MCP</div>
			<div class="arch-row" style="margin-top:8px;">
				<div class="arch-node teal" style="flex:1; max-width:420px;">
					<div style="font-size:13px;">memtomem-stm (STM Proxy)</div>
					<div style="font-size:11px; margin-top:4px; opacity:0.8;">CLEAN → COMPRESS → SURFACE → INDEX</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div style="display:flex; justify-content:center; gap:40px; margin:8px 0;">
				<div class="arch-arrow">↕ Surfacing</div>
				<div class="arch-arrow">↕ MCP</div>
			</div>
			<div class="arch-row">
				<div class="arch-node accent" style="flex:1; max-width:260px;">
					<div style="font-size:13px;">memtomem (LTM)</div>
					<div style="font-size:11px; margin-top:4px; opacity:0.8;">74 MCP Tools</div>
				</div>
				<div class="arch-node" style="flex:1; max-width:260px;">
					<div style="font-size:13px;">Upstream MCP Servers</div>
					<div style="font-size:11px; margin-top:4px; opacity:0.7;">filesystem, GitHub, …</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section class="section">
	<div class="section-inner">
		<div class="section-label">Compatibility</div>
		<div class="section-title">Supported Runtimes & Frameworks</div>
		<div class="section-desc">MCP-native — works with any MCP-compatible client.</div>
		<div class="runtime-grid">
			<div class="runtime-chip">Claude Code</div>
			<div class="runtime-chip">Cursor</div>
			<div class="runtime-chip">Windsurf</div>
			<div class="runtime-chip">Claude Desktop</div>
			<div class="runtime-chip">Gemini CLI</div>
			<div class="runtime-chip">Codex CLI</div>
			<div class="runtime-chip">Antigravity</div>
			<div class="runtime-chip">LangGraph</div>
			<div class="runtime-chip">CrewAI</div>
			<div class="runtime-chip">LangChain</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section class="section">
	<div class="section-inner">
		<div class="section-label">Documentation</div>
		<div class="section-title">Docs & Tutorials</div>
		<div class="section-desc">From getting started to advanced usage.</div>
		<div class="docs-grid">
			<a href={`${base}/en/guides/quickstart/`} class="doc-card">
				<h3>Quick Start</h3>
				<p>From install to first memory in under 5 minutes. uv install → MCP setup → search.</p>
				<span class="tag tag-guide">Guide</span>
			</a>
			<a href={`${base}/en/ltm/hybrid-search/`} class="doc-card">
				<h3>Hybrid Search</h3>
				<p>How BM25 + vector + RRF fusion search works and how to tune it.</p>
				<span class="tag tag-ltm">LTM</span>
			</a>
			<a href={`${base}/en/stm/compression/`} class="doc-card">
				<h3>Compression Strategies</h3>
				<p>10 strategies, auto-selection logic, and query-aware budget allocation.</p>
				<span class="tag tag-stm">STM</span>
			</a>
			<a href={`${base}/en/stm/surfacing/`} class="doc-card">
				<h3>Proactive Surfacing</h3>
				<p>5-level gating, feedback loop, min_score auto-tuning deep dive.</p>
				<span class="tag tag-stm">STM</span>
			</a>
			<a href={`${base}/en/ltm/multi-agent/`} class="doc-card">
				<h3>Multi-Agent Collaboration</h3>
				<p>Namespace design, agent_register/search/share workflows.</p>
				<span class="tag tag-ltm">LTM</span>
			</a>
			<a href={`${base}/en/stm/context-gateway/`} class="doc-card">
				<h3>Context Gateway</h3>
				<p>Cross-runtime sync, format conversion, LangGraph adapter.</p>
				<span class="tag tag-guide">Guide</span>
			</a>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section class="cta-section">
	<h2>Get Started Now</h2>
	<p>No GPU. No external services. One uv install is all you need.</p>
	<div class="cta-buttons">
		<a href="https://github.com/memtomem/memtomem">
			<button class="btn-primary">View on GitHub</button>
		</a>
		<a href={`${base}/en/guides/quickstart/`}>
			<button class="btn-secondary">Read the Docs</button>
		</a>
	</div>
</section>

<footer class="footer">
	<span>DAPADA Inc. — Apache 2.0</span>
	<span>
		<a href="https://github.com/memtomem/memtomem" style="color:inherit;">GitHub</a>
		&nbsp;·&nbsp;
		<a href="https://pypi.org/project/memtomem/" style="color:inherit;">PyPI</a>
	</span>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
